physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Anterior and septal myocardial infarction; presence of myocardial edema; left ventricular global systolic function preserved with an ejection fraction of 56%; mildly reduced left ventricular global systolic function with an ejection fraction of 45% observed.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The anterior myocardial area is likely chronic, while the inferior wall infarction is suggested to be acute.
